data.meta_description: Welcome to our Meet The Team page. Contact Complete Dental Health Center of South Carolina today at (843) 487-5156 or visit our office servicing Dillon, South Carolina
data.text:
Dr. Neda Emad-Azmoudeh

DDS

Joined Team CDCSC 2018

Dr. Neda Emad-Azmoudeh was born in Tehran, Iran. She migrated to the United States in 1986. She is a 1989 graduate of Maryland University, Pre dental. Dr. Emad completed her Doctor of Dental Surgery (DDS) degree in 1993 at the notable Howard University located in Washington, DC. She has been practicing dentistry for over 27 years.

Personal Life

Dr. Neda Emad-Azmoudeh has been happily married to her husband Kevin for the past 34 years. Together they are the proud parents of two beautiful children. In her free time, Dr. Emad enjoys exploring the city of Florence, SC, taking walks, swimming, and trying out new restaurants around town.

Favorite Quote

“One loyal friend worth thousand acquaintance.”

Organizations

She is a member of the American Dental Association, South Carolina Dental Association, and Virginia Dental Association.

Dr. Veronica Mathis

DMD

Dr. Veronica Mathis

Joined Team CDCSC 2022

Veronica Mathis DMD

Dr. Veronica Mathis, originally from Clinton, North Carolina, graduated from Meredith College in Raleigh, North Carolina before receiving her Doctorate in 1998 from the University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey. She was selected to complete a multi-disciplinary hospital residency at Harlem Hospital Center in New York City. This residency provided her with advanced training in all the specialties of dentistry including oral surgery, endodontics and treatment of medically compromised patients. Dr. Mathis has been practicing general dentistry for over 23 years in New York, New Jersey and Pennsylvania. Now she is back in the Carolina's and with us here at Comprehensive Dental Center of South Carolina!

Personal Life

She loves spending time with her son, Nathan. She enjoys traveling, road trips and photographing her adventures.

Favorite Quote

Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding. In all your ways acknowledge him and he will make your paths straight. (Proverbs 3:5)

Organizations

She is a member of the American Dental Association and New Jersey Dental Association.

Ms. Amber Simpson
